| Veterinary Medicine | Nicole King Allen |

### Additional Counselors Referenced

- Shehla Hajiani: Citizenship in the Community (planned to teach after Woodruff 2024)
- Allatoona Aquatics Base: Lifesaving merit badge
- Troop encourages each registered adult to become an MB counselor for one Eagle-required badge (~6 hours/year commitment)

## Merit Badge Opportunities

### Summer Camp (Woodruff Scout Camp)

- Primary venue for earning merit badges, especially Eagle-required ones
- Advice from leadership: schedule MBs daily (morning and afternoon); aim for at least 2 Eagle-required MBs
- Avoid aquatic MBs at Woodruff since most are available at Allatoona Aquatics Base on Saturdays over the summer
- Exception: Water Sports (water skiing/wakeboarding) only at Woodruff
- Prioritize First Aid MB if not yet completed
- Note age requirements on some MBs

### Allatoona Aquatics Base

- Saturday merit badge clinics throughout summer
- Swimming, canoeing, fishing, kayaking MBs available
- Lifesaving MB available here
- Website: https://www.scoutingatl.org/caabmb

### Conservation Weekend (Woodruff, November)

- Merit badges offered (historically): Bird Study, Energy, Environmental Science, Fish & Wildlife Management, Fishing, Forestry, Fly Fishing, Geology, Landscape Architecture, Mammal Study, Nature, Nuclear Science, Oceanography, Plant Science, Pulp and Paper, Reptile & Amphibian Study, Soil and Water Conservation, Sustainability, Weather
- Only 1 Eagle-required MB typically offered: Environmental Science (age requirement ~13)
- Cost: ~$100/Scout, ~$75/adult

### External Opportunities

- Eagle Merit Badge Summit (February)
- Troop 370 Merit Badge Summit (February)
- Porsche Automotive Maintenance Merit Badge Day
- STEM Merit Badge Summit (April)
- Personal Management Merit Badge Day (September)
- Stranger Things Merit Badge Summit (October, KSU Marietta)
- Scoutland Pathfinder MB clinics (June)

## Service Hours

- Must be approved in advance by Advancement Chair or Scoutmaster
- **Pre-approved:** Scout troop/district/council events (Conservation Weekend, Troop 370 MB Clinic, Cub-a-Ree, etc.) and official ICGL-sponsored service events
- Service hours cannot be double-counted for both Pace Academy and Scouts

## Cooking Tracking

A dedicated cooking tracking system managed by Jenny Beauchamp (ptjenny76@yahoo.com) covers:
- Cooking for rank advancement (Tenderfoot 2a/2b/2c, Second Class 2e, First Class 2a-2e)
- Cooking Merit Badge requirements (5a-5g camp cooking, 6a-6f trail/backpacking meals)
- Camping Merit Badge cooking requirements (8c, 8d)

## EDGE Method for Life Rank

The troop tracks EDGE (Explain, Demonstrate, Guide, Enable) teaching requirements for Life rank. Specific skill areas are assigned to senior Scouts to teach newer Scouts:
- First aid (Tenderfoot/Second Class/First Class requirements)
- Cooking and tools
- Navigation
- Lashings and camp gadgets

## Order of the Arrow Eligibility

**Requirements:**
- First Class rank or above
- 15 camping nights in the last 2 years (tracked in Scoutbook)
- Must include a long-term (5-night) camping experience

**Process:**
- Troop elections held during a regular meeting (need majority of troop in attendance)
- Spring 2026 election: March 31 meeting

## Eagle-Required Merit Badges (14 total)

1. First Aid
2. Citizenship in the Community
3. Citizenship in the Nation
4. Citizenship in Society
5. Citizenship in the World
6. Communication
7. Cooking
8. Personal Fitness
9. Emergency Preparedness OR Lifesaving
10. Environmental Science OR Sustainability
11. Personal Management
12. Swimming OR Hiking OR Cycling
13. Camping
14. Family Life

Total of 21 merit badges needed for Eagle (14 required + 7 elective).

